<HEADLINE>
COMPULSORY MILITARY SERVICE TO BE SHORTENED TO 14 MONTHS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 15 (CNA) 03/15/07  13:30:54 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian said Thursday that compulsory military
service will be shortened to 14 months from the present 16 months
starting July 1.
</P>
<P>
President Chen, in his capacity as the commander-in-chief of the
armed forces, made the remarks while attending a tea party for
the nominees for a public service award for youths.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that he hopes the ratio of volunteer recruits will
account for 60 percent of the armed forces by the end of this
year and that compulsory military service will be further
shortened to 12 months by Jan. 1, 2008.
</P>
